name: Wanna Grill
address: Jl. Basangalas, Tri Buana, Kec. Abang, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80852, Indonesia
review 1: This place is a secret treasure of Bali. The food and drinks are very tasty and traditional. The view is simply amazing! Looking at the green rice fields, time slows down and the sight is truly peaceful. If you want a really local and very special experience, I recommend visiting this place. The extreme kindness and hospitality of the villagers is also special.
review 2:

The fries are exactly perfection, like Belgian fries. Fresh potatoes and perfectly fried.

review 3: This is an trully oasis in such a touristic place - good prices, good meal, quite location amazing service and stunning view. Definitely will come back next time and recommend to my friends to visit.
review 4:
Such an amazing place with delicious food.
Probably the most delicious food we ate in Bali, overlooking picturesque rice fields.

The food was delicious, the portions were plentiful, and the service was very friendly, offering free tea, water, peanuts, and watermelon. Serving real fresh juice.
review 5:
Amazing little gem hidden between some rice fields, with a stunning authentic view. You gotta keep an eye out for the roadsigns, because the path to enter is either between two buildings, or at the end of the village and around the buildings, along the rice paddies.

The two guys working there definetly made us feel comfortable with our little baby daughter. We were lucky to arrive and stay there the entire stay alone. So humbling.

We got refreshments for free as a compliment, and great service.
We enjoyed the bbq ribs with fries, and double up for both on the watermelon juice! Give us more!

We are already planing to come back tomorrow.

Prices are great, staff is great, the ricefield view is top.

name: Wanna Sunrise volcano & rice view
address: HJX8+FRH, Jl. Basangalas, Tri Buana, Kec. Abang, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80852, Indonesia
review 1: Wonderfull view of mount Agun on the way of Lampuyan temple. Traditional paddy field cultivation.
review 2: I did this as part of a tour, I was picked up from my hotel early in the morning to make the moosy of the sunrise over the mountains and to get amazing pictures at the gates of heaven, the whole tour was about 8/9 hours and that included stopping off at an amazing treetop restaurant for lunch, I would highly recommend Dwipa for a tour +62 821-4507-9737 very reasonable and a very knowledgeable man whom was a total gentleman, you won't be disappointed
review 3: Have 2 views, one to mount agung, and the other to mount seraya, we can see Lempuyang temple at top of the mountain in a distance
review 4: You can see the best view at 5.00 am until sunset.  Drive with #BaliCabTaxi
review 5: rice fields with a beautiful village nearby

name: Basangalas Mount Agung Rice View
address: HJX8+HQC, Tri Buana, Abang, Karangasem Regency, Bali 80852, Indonesia
review 1: Very good place to see sunrise with Mountain Agung view
review 2: One of my favorite places in Bali! Great place with nice view and the background of Agung Volcano!
review 3: Sadly there were clouds but its really beautiful.
